<LP>
   ATLANTA -- First Financial Management Corp. said that its
board of directors authorized the purchase of up to $90
million of the company's common stock.
   The financial services concern said it will buy shares in
both open-market and private transactions.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company said its shares are "greatly undervalued" at
the current stock price. In New York Stock Exchange composite
trading yesterday, First Financial's shares closed at $20.50,
up $1.75.
